<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Clarification - PvP Zone is for no level limits only</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:49 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Clarification - PvP Zone is for no level limits only<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=420" TARGET=_self>a lot of us need to take a new perspective then</A> (Tempra[CC])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>By a PvP zone I mean one that ignores level limits, not one that goes around the established need for a PvP switch. If a zone were made that totally ignored the PvP switch and allowed random violence, it would have to be a new zone stuck off in a far corner with a big sign posted at the entrance saying "Land of Death Beyond" or something to that effect. In any case I don't expect 989 to bypass the PvP swtich even if a new zone were added. The idea is simply to allow PvP players to fight without level restrictions somewhere in the game.
<P>&gt; When i suggested the grogg and oggok areas i had only pvp+
<BR>&gt; server in mind. Rpers wont like that. it is a bit late for them
<BR>&gt; to make 1 to 2 zones that are just everyone becomes pvp+ for. It
<BR>&gt; will be hard maintaining this all on one server. People will
<BR>&gt; yell if you make a place such as Najena a pvp+ area because non
<BR>&gt; pvp type people want to explore and fight in that area of the
<BR>&gt; world. Having free zones right now are almost impossible for
<BR>&gt; both parties to agree on unless a new zone is dedicated just to
<BR>&gt; pvp+ which i dont think they have the time to do.
<P>&gt; Anything we discuss here should keep in mind that it is intended
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
